# Using error codes

Angular actually adds the error codes on the individual controls on the errors object. 

You can access the codes with the get method.

# Example

signupForm.get('userData.username').errors['nameIsForbidden']
Will return true if the control contains the error 'nameIsForbidden'

# Remember

These error codes can be used to show the right error messages and of course you can come up with more complex set ups.